de.tud.kom.p2psim.api.common
Interface HostProperties

All Superinterfaces:
ComponentEventListener, ConnectivityListener
All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultHostProperties
public interface HostProperties
extends ConnectivityListener

Provides Methods to get some cross-layer information about a host. There are many possible properties like the geographical position, maximum and current upload rate, maximum and current download rate. Note that depending on the actual components of a host some properties may be empty, e.g. the euclidian point may be unknown/unset.

Additionally, the host properties can be used to track the connectivity status of a host by registering a ConnectivityListener with it.

Despite the cross-layer information host properties is used to enable the churn per host.
